div.div: These are a few free-form communication channels and some links to information about Fedora's release parties and annual conferences. Fedorans regularly come together to celebrate our community and the hard work that we put into it!

a.class: col-span-1 p-4 cursor-default rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
a.div: This is the Fedora Project's annual contributor conference. Don't miss this opportunity to meet other Fedora contributors in-person and find out what is happening in the project!

a.class: col-span-1 p-4 cursor-default rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
a.div: This is the proverbial office water cooler, where people gather for break from work conversation. Introduce yourself, have (friendly!) off-topic discussions, and socialize!

a.class: col-span-1 p-4 cursor-default rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
a.div: The Fedora Social chat room is a place for Fedora community members to relax and talk about most any topics they wish.

a.class: col-span-1 p-4 cursor-default rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
a.div: Beyond the official channels for Fedorans to communicate, community members are involved on other popular platforms as well! Check out IRC, Discord, Telegram, Reddit, and more!

a.class: col-span-1 p-4 cursor-default rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
a.div: This is a week in September where we highlight the contributions and experiences of women, lgbtq+, and bipoc in Fedora.

a.class: col-span-1 p-4 cursor-default rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
a.div: Fedora releases two major versions every year. We celebrate the hard work of our contributors virtually at each release.
